article.headline: Toledo 68, Marshall 65
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio (AP) -- Keith Triplett had 18 points and six rebounds, and Toledo withstood a late rally to beat Marshall 68-65 Wednesday night. Triplett's two freethrows with 48 seconds left put Toledo (10-3, 4-1 Mid American Conference) ahead by 11 points at 67-56 before the Thundering Herd (5-7, 2-3) went on a 9-1 run to close the game. Marshall's Tre Whitted made two 3-pointers and Enoch Bunch hit a third in the game's final 18 seconds. Whitted finished with 10 points, while Bunch scored five. Eric Smith had 13 points and 11 rebounds for Marshall. The Rockets' A.J. Shellebarger added 16 points and 10 rebounds. Toledo led 31-25 at halftime and stayed ahead throughout the entire second half. The Rockets shot 44.8 percent from the floor, while the Thundering Herd's field goal percentage was 38.1.
